===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{context|countable|lang=en}} An [[excessive]] [[amount]] of something.
#: ''A '''surfeit''' of wheat is driving down the price.''
# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} [[overindulgence|Overindulgence]] in either [[food]] or [[drink]]; [[overeat]]ing.
#* Shakespeare
#*: Now comes the sick hour that his '''surfeit''' made.
# {{context|countable|lang=en}} A [[sickness]] or condition caused by overindulgence.
#: ''King Henry I is said to have died of a '''surfeit''' of lampreys.''
#* Bunyan
#*: to prevent '''surfeit''' and other diseases that are incident to those that heat their blood by travels
# Disgust caused by excess; [[satiety]].
#* Burke
#*: Matter and argument have been supplied abundantly, and even to '''surfeit'''.
#: {{rfquotek|Sir Philip Sidney}}

